pageContext.claim: “For the first time in American history, we have replaced a disastrous trade deal that rewarded outsourcing with a truly fair and reciprocal trade deal that will keep jobs, wealth, and growth right here in America.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump tends to characterize all trade deals that he did not negotiate as “disastrous” but that doesn't mean the U.S. has never before altered or changed a trade deal. Trump has already done so during his first term.
